  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nWe seem to support writing Typescript tests in some form, but the details are unclear and it seems to be barely documented.  There's a [section](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/testing/writing-tests-in-javascript#typescript-file-support) for it on the page on writing Javascript tests, but it says basically nothing -- the \"see for more\" link in it just links back to the top of the same page!\r\n\r\nAlso, similar to @gnidan's idea in trufflesuite/trufflesuite.com#1397 that there should be a \"supported languages\" page, maybe there should similarly be a \"supported testing languages\" page?",
